WEBVTT

00:07.374 --> 00:07.908
‐ Previously on "The Purge"...

00:08.909 --> 00:10.511
This doesn't have
the same weight it used to.

00:10.544 --> 00:11.278
‐ It's a new world out there.

00:11.311 --> 00:12.746
I chose to adapt.
‐ Well, so am I.

00:12.779 --> 00:13.881
The banks put the money
in the air.

00:13.914 --> 00:17.818
We can take it before
it ever leaves the ground.

00:17.851 --> 00:18.619
Can you get us to the vaults

00:18.652 --> 00:20.954
that get loaded
onto the airplanes?

00:20.988 --> 00:22.456
‐ You do know how to dream big.

00:22.489 --> 00:23.390
‐ Jammer's in place.

00:23.423 --> 00:26.093
[device beeps]
[electricity crackles]

00:26.126 --> 00:27.194
‐ Somebody put a bounty
on your head.

00:27.227 --> 00:29.429
‐ Cases like these,
it's someone you know.

00:29.463 --> 00:31.431
‐ Ivory Road,
it's a trading post

00:31.465 --> 00:32.533
for illegal activity.

00:32.566 --> 00:34.468
‐ Have you Purged before?
‐ Yeah.

00:34.501 --> 00:35.302
‐ There's nothing
to be ashamed of.

00:35.335 --> 00:37.137
‐ [grunts]

00:37.170 --> 00:39.006
‐ This is that missing farmer
stuff you've been following.

00:39.039 --> 00:41.108
‐ Heatstroke
the cause of death.

00:41.141 --> 00:43.343
‐ I'm looking for Olivia.
[gasps]

00:43.377 --> 00:45.145
‐ Olivia's case
has been closed.

00:45.178 --> 00:46.013
The coroner ruled it
a suicide.

00:46.046 --> 00:47.447
‐ Well, that's not right.

00:47.481 --> 00:48.382
‐ I know your sister
was troubled.

00:48.415 --> 00:50.551
‐ How do you know
about my sister?

00:50.584 --> 00:53.687
[intense music]

00:53.720 --> 00:56.523
[horns honking,
indistinct chatter]

00:59.493 --> 01:02.195
[women speaking Portuguese]

01:10.170 --> 01:12.673
‐ [speaking Portuguese]

01:25.152 --> 01:27.521
Ah, "Dirty Harry."

01:27.554 --> 01:30.290
Make my day, partner.
[squelches]

02:32.285 --> 02:35.255
[dramatic music]

02:35.288 --> 02:42.195
♪ ♪

02:48.268 --> 02:51.271
[suspenseful music]

02:51.304 --> 02:58.311
♪ ♪

03:08.188 --> 03:10.290
‐ Can you hear me okay?

03:10.323 --> 03:12.626
‐ Loud and clear.
Don't waste time.

03:12.659 --> 03:15.295
Just get to the safe,
plant the device.

03:15.328 --> 03:18.131
♪ ♪

03:18.165 --> 03:19.599
‐ Good morning.

03:19.633 --> 03:21.368
This way, please.

03:21.401 --> 03:27.607
♪ ♪

03:27.641 --> 03:30.444
Wait here. The Barkers
will be right with you.

03:30.477 --> 03:32.813
♪ ♪

03:32.846 --> 03:35.449
‐ Ah, Mr. and Mrs. Barker.

03:35.482 --> 03:37.150
So good to meet you.

03:37.184 --> 03:38.318
‐ Hi.
‐ Hi.

03:38.351 --> 03:42.189
[clears throat] The brushwork
on this is magnificent.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.957
‐ Family heirloom.

03:43.990 --> 03:46.293
Just had it refurbished.

03:46.326 --> 03:48.462
‐ Late 1800s, am I right?

03:48.495 --> 03:49.429
Lovely composition.

03:49.463 --> 03:52.165
I'm guessing the painter
was, uh, plein air.

03:52.199 --> 03:54.701
‐ I miss Tommy.
‐ Tell me about it.

03:54.735 --> 03:58.271
‐ Uh, well, shall we?

03:58.305 --> 03:59.306
‐ Shall we what?

03:59.339 --> 04:01.541
‐ Assess the items
in your bank safe.

04:01.575 --> 04:03.310
‐ We don't need to go up there.

04:03.343 --> 04:05.312
‐ We have our own people
for that.

04:05.345 --> 04:08.181
‐ Here is an itemized list
of its contents.

04:08.215 --> 04:09.116
Current value.

04:09.149 --> 04:11.485
Total's right there
at the bottom.

04:11.518 --> 04:14.855
‐ But the bank sent me
personally to do an appraisal.

04:15.922 --> 04:17.257
‐ Easy visit for you, then.

04:17.290 --> 04:19.359
‐ Oh, shit.

04:19.392 --> 04:22.496
‐ I'm not sure this list is
going to be enough for my boss.

04:22.529 --> 04:24.698
‐ If it's not,
have him call me.

04:24.731 --> 04:26.500
[tense music]

04:26.533 --> 04:29.302
Or I can just talk to him
next time we play golf.

04:29.336 --> 04:31.671
♪ ♪

04:31.705 --> 04:33.607
‐ Of course.

04:33.640 --> 04:35.842
‐ We'll call you
when it's ready for pickup.

04:35.876 --> 04:37.544
♪ ♪

04:37.577 --> 04:38.545
‐ Thank you.

04:38.578 --> 04:40.247
‐ Good‐bye, now.

04:40.280 --> 04:47.320
♪ ♪

04:51.291 --> 04:53.426
‐ I got a good price on these.

04:53.460 --> 04:56.963
‐ I scheduled some range time
with the instructor on Sunday.

04:56.997 --> 04:58.498
‐ Oh, thanks, babe.
‐ Mm‐hmm.

04:58.532 --> 05:01.568
‐ PI changed the meeting.
They want to meet at 5:30.

05:01.601 --> 05:03.436
Does that work for you?

05:03.470 --> 05:06.439
‐ Uh, yeah, I'm good.

05:07.908 --> 05:10.243
Grab a bite after?
‐ Sure.

05:11.478 --> 05:13.814
‐ Maybe, uh, somewhere nice,

05:13.847 --> 05:15.715
like date night.

05:16.950 --> 05:19.052
‐ Oh, yeah, you're right.

05:19.085 --> 05:20.754
It's been a while.
I'm sorry.

05:20.787 --> 05:22.622
‐ No, Marcus, no.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.324
You're dealing with so much
right now.

05:24.357 --> 05:26.326
You don't have to apologize.

05:26.359 --> 05:29.229
I was just thinking
it could be good for us

05:29.262 --> 05:31.798
to try and remember
what it's like

05:31.832 --> 05:33.800
to feel normal, you know?

05:33.834 --> 05:35.702
‐ I want that too, yeah?

05:35.735 --> 05:37.737
[cell phone chimes]

05:37.771 --> 05:40.340
‐ [sighs] Oh,
maybe you should answer that.

05:40.373 --> 05:42.475
What if it's the investigator?

05:42.509 --> 05:43.743
‐ Yeah.

05:43.777 --> 05:50.617
♪ ♪

06:05.332 --> 06:07.934
‐ So, uh, you ladies go out
on Halloween?

06:07.968 --> 06:09.169
Scare up some trouble?

06:09.202 --> 06:11.771
‐ Kelen made me do a
"Harry Potter" thing with her.

06:11.805 --> 06:13.273
[both laugh]
‐ I made you?

06:13.306 --> 06:14.875
You wanted to.

06:14.908 --> 06:16.610
‐ I just stayed in,
read a book.

06:16.643 --> 06:19.379
Boring, I know.
‐ No, no, I love books.

06:19.412 --> 06:21.681
I'm finally getting around
to some classics, actually.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.383
‐ What are you reading?

06:23.416 --> 06:24.417
‐ Um, I'm halfway through

06:24.451 --> 06:26.853
Dr. Updale's "Foundations
of the Experiment."

06:26.887 --> 06:29.456
Unauthorized.

06:29.489 --> 06:31.691
I'm kind of a history buff.

06:31.725 --> 06:34.828
‐ NFFA history?
‐ Yeah, it was a best seller.

06:34.861 --> 06:36.763
The part about giving in
to your worst urges

06:36.796 --> 06:39.032
as a form of military service
is just...

06:39.065 --> 06:41.668
[imitates explosion]
Wow.

06:41.701 --> 06:43.036
‐ Didn't she kill herself

06:43.069 --> 06:44.971
after creating
the first Purge Night?

06:45.005 --> 06:47.374
‐ No, that's been debunked.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.308
She died Purging.

06:48.341 --> 06:50.977
‐ Well, you would know.
‐ [laughs]

06:51.011 --> 06:54.414
I can recommend some books
if you want to look into it.

06:54.447 --> 06:56.049
I have most of them
back in my dorm.

06:56.082 --> 06:58.885
‐ Uh, maybe.
‐ Yeah?

07:01.021 --> 07:03.790
‐ Uh, Andy,
get us some refills?

07:03.823 --> 07:05.358
‐ Sure.

07:05.392 --> 07:06.826
All right.
‐ Thanks, man.

07:08.862 --> 07:10.096
‐ I'm so sorry.

07:10.130 --> 07:11.498
This was Ben's idea.

07:11.531 --> 07:13.500
‐ What?
Why are you sorry?

07:13.533 --> 07:16.036
‐ Because we hooked her up
with a weirdo.

07:16.069 --> 07:18.672
It's basically like listening
to Bobby Sheridan.

07:18.705 --> 07:20.707
Everything is about the Purge.

07:20.740 --> 07:21.574
‐ Is that what you think?

07:21.608 --> 07:23.777
‐ Honestly, I would have
already left,

07:23.810 --> 07:26.012
but I don't want to end up
on his hit list.

07:26.046 --> 07:27.881
‐ I don't trust him.

07:27.914 --> 07:30.717
He just feels off, you know?

07:30.750 --> 07:32.419
‐ He's been cool to me.

07:32.452 --> 07:35.522
‐ Well, you tell him it's not
gonna work with Bonnie.

07:37.223 --> 07:39.759
‐ Fine.
‐ All right.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.128
Two diet Sprites
for the ladies.

07:42.162 --> 07:43.863
‐ Thanks.
‐ Mm‐hmm.

07:43.897 --> 07:46.166
What'd I miss?

07:48.068 --> 07:50.971
[indistinct chatter]

07:51.004 --> 07:54.574
[phone rings]

07:57.577 --> 08:00.580
[computer beeping]

08:03.083 --> 08:04.818
‐ Esme.

08:04.851 --> 08:06.720
‐ Uh, yeah, what's up?

08:06.753 --> 08:08.822
‐ Do you have those stats yet?
‐ Stats?

08:08.855 --> 08:12.926
Yeah, uh, no, I‐‐
I'm working on it.

08:12.959 --> 08:15.996
‐ Okay, um, I need them
in an hour.

08:16.029 --> 08:18.131
‐ Sure thing.

08:21.001 --> 08:24.004
[dark music]

08:24.037 --> 08:27.474
♪ ♪

08:27.507 --> 08:29.009
[door clicks open]
Hello!

08:29.042 --> 08:30.577
‐ [speaking Spanish]

08:31.511 --> 08:32.812
‐ [speaking Spanish]

08:32.846 --> 08:35.782
♪ ♪

08:50.964 --> 08:54.034
‐ Sofia, get out here!

08:56.302 --> 08:57.804
[knocking]

08:57.837 --> 08:59.239
‐ What do you want?

09:01.875 --> 09:04.644
‐ I don't understand Spanish.
‐ [laughs]

09:05.812 --> 09:08.948
What's going on with you?
Come on, help me clean up.

09:08.982 --> 09:11.818
‐ You're not Amá.
Stop trying to be.

09:11.851 --> 09:13.987
♪ ♪

09:14.020 --> 09:15.121
[door slams]

09:15.155 --> 09:17.624
‐ Hey, what is this?

09:17.657 --> 09:19.559
Oh, perfect.

09:19.592 --> 09:22.295
What the fuck are you doing?
What are you not telling me?

09:22.328 --> 09:24.531
‐ Nothing.
‐ "Nothing"?

09:24.564 --> 09:26.299
It's always nothing with you.

09:26.332 --> 09:27.600
♪ ♪

09:27.634 --> 09:31.037
‐ Remember that night that
Amá was at the hospital?

09:31.071 --> 09:33.239
The night that she‐‐
‐ Yes, I remember.

09:33.273 --> 09:35.508
‐ She told me
that Apá was sick

09:35.542 --> 09:37.710
and that sometimes he gets sad.

09:37.744 --> 09:39.579
‐ Well, he's depressed.

09:39.612 --> 09:40.914
‐ Why does he get to be
the only one who's hurting?

09:40.947 --> 09:43.416
‐ That's not fair.
I am hurting too.

09:43.450 --> 09:46.252
[stammers] Is that why
you're taking these?

09:46.286 --> 09:48.822
‐ I don't know.

09:48.855 --> 09:50.990
‐ What's wrong?

09:51.024 --> 09:52.192
Talk to me.
Come on.

09:52.225 --> 09:54.060
‐ Ow.

09:54.094 --> 09:57.230
♪ ♪

09:57.263 --> 09:59.933
‐ What's that?
Show me.

09:59.966 --> 10:06.272
♪ ♪

10:06.306 --> 10:09.209
What is this from?

10:09.242 --> 10:11.044
Huh?

10:11.077 --> 10:16.015
♪ ♪

10:16.049 --> 10:18.885
What?

10:18.918 --> 10:20.253
‐ They're from Apá.

10:20.286 --> 10:26.326
♪ ♪

10:27.994 --> 10:30.063
‐ [exhales shakily]

10:30.096 --> 10:33.032
♪ ♪

10:33.066 --> 10:35.068
Oh, my God.

10:35.101 --> 10:38.304
♪ ♪

10:38.338 --> 10:40.306
How long?

10:40.340 --> 10:42.075
‐ You believe me?

10:42.108 --> 10:45.211
‐ Of course.
How long?

10:45.245 --> 10:47.046
♪ ♪

10:47.080 --> 10:49.549
‐ It started
right after Amá died.

10:49.582 --> 10:52.252
The more he drinks,
the worse it gets.

10:52.285 --> 10:53.953
♪ ♪

10:53.987 --> 10:56.823
And I'm the only one here now.

10:56.856 --> 10:58.791
You're the one
who got to leave.

11:00.160 --> 11:02.128
‐ Oh, God, no.

11:02.162 --> 11:06.099
♪ ♪

11:06.132 --> 11:08.635
We're getting
the hell out of here.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.236
Get your stuff.

11:10.270 --> 11:13.673
♪ ♪

11:13.706 --> 11:15.742
[keys clacking]

11:17.277 --> 11:19.879
‐ I pulled the architectural
plans for the Barker house.

11:19.913 --> 11:21.314
‐ What's our time frame?

11:21.347 --> 11:23.183
How long do we have
to get Sara's jammer in place?

11:23.216 --> 11:24.284
‐ It's gotta be back
at the bank in a week.

11:24.317 --> 11:25.151
‐ That soon?

11:25.185 --> 11:26.619
‐ Well, usually
the Purge vaults

11:26.653 --> 11:27.687
don't ever leave the bank.

11:27.720 --> 11:29.255
The only reason these two
got home delivery at all

11:29.289 --> 11:30.089
was NFFA connections.

11:30.123 --> 11:31.257
‐ Okay, okay,
let's back up here.

11:31.291 --> 11:33.793
Now we're talking about
breaking and entering

11:33.826 --> 11:35.028
off‐Purge?

11:35.061 --> 11:36.663
‐ Well, that was always
plan B.

11:36.696 --> 11:39.165
‐ Okay, well, I'm still on
plan A: nothing illegal.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.166
That's the whole reason

11:40.200 --> 11:41.901
why we got Tommy's guy on
in the first place.

11:41.935 --> 11:43.870
‐ Hey, "Tommy's guy"
is getting you access

11:43.903 --> 11:45.805
to a safe that's gonna be
on the Purge Night plane.

11:45.838 --> 11:48.408
‐ Okay, well, you were supposed
to get the jammer in it.

11:48.441 --> 11:52.011
We get caught doing this,
it is a crime.

11:52.045 --> 11:54.714
‐ As long as we're unarmed
it's a minor offense, level Y.

11:54.747 --> 11:56.216
‐ Heist is fucked
if we don't try this.

11:56.249 --> 11:58.384
‐ Well, the heist will be
fucked if we're in prison.

11:58.418 --> 12:00.320
‐ Guys, this house,
it's hidden from the street.

12:00.353 --> 12:02.822
There's minimal cameras.
I'll play lookout.

12:02.855 --> 12:04.290
‐ We gotta find our window.

12:04.324 --> 12:07.227
It's a big property,
probably have staff working.

12:07.260 --> 12:09.362
‐ Every Saturday,
they go and play golf.

12:09.395 --> 12:10.964
No groundskeepers
that day either.

12:10.997 --> 12:12.098
I'm telling you,
I did my research.

12:12.131 --> 12:14.133
‐ I could follow them
and radio when they get back.

12:14.167 --> 12:15.101
‐ See that there?

12:15.134 --> 12:17.170
That‐‐that's the kind
of creative brainstorming

12:17.203 --> 12:18.404
that we need right now.

12:18.438 --> 12:20.139
‐ Doug, why are you okay
with this?

12:20.173 --> 12:21.874
‐ 'Cause I wanna be done
with this kind of work.

12:21.908 --> 12:23.409
This is our only shot
at pulling this off.

12:23.443 --> 12:24.777
‐ We need to get in that safe,

12:24.811 --> 12:28.014
or we have no way to stop
the planes on Purge Night.

12:28.047 --> 12:29.816
It's now or never.

12:33.486 --> 12:33.853
[suspenseful music]

12:36.256 --> 12:43.296
♪ ♪

12:44.197 --> 12:46.532
‐ Marcus Moore.

12:46.566 --> 12:49.168
Albert.

12:49.202 --> 12:51.337
‐ So what are you looking
to score?

12:51.371 --> 12:53.573
Oxy like everybody else
on the site?

12:53.606 --> 12:55.108
‐ No, no, no.

12:55.141 --> 12:56.376
Call me old‐fashioned.

12:56.409 --> 13:01.214
I'd rather enjoy the emotional
highs and lows of daily life.

13:01.247 --> 13:04.550
‐ So, uh, what, then?

13:04.584 --> 13:06.786
‐ I read your story.

13:06.819 --> 13:09.122
It stuck with me.

13:09.155 --> 13:10.123
‐ Right.

13:10.156 --> 13:12.225
So can you get me a name?

13:12.258 --> 13:13.693
‐ I can.

13:13.726 --> 13:16.195
♪ ♪

13:16.229 --> 13:18.264
But names have consequences,

13:18.298 --> 13:20.867
and they come at a price.

13:20.900 --> 13:22.769
‐ So how much do you want?

13:22.802 --> 13:25.204
How does this work?
How do I pay you?

13:25.238 --> 13:26.806
♪ ♪

13:26.839 --> 13:29.309
‐ Let's just say
there are a lot of people

13:29.342 --> 13:31.277
who require a doctor.

13:31.311 --> 13:35.715
♪ ♪

13:44.757 --> 13:46.726
[knock at door]

13:46.759 --> 13:48.261
‐ [sighs]

13:52.165 --> 13:53.533
[lock slides]

13:54.834 --> 13:57.804
[soft music]

13:57.837 --> 14:01.140
♪ ♪

14:01.174 --> 14:03.443
[door slams]
[lock clicks]

14:03.476 --> 14:04.811
‐ Did you take the route
I asked?

14:04.844 --> 14:06.679
‐ Yeah, I know
how to be discreet.

14:06.713 --> 14:07.680
[lock clicks]

14:07.714 --> 14:10.583
Looks like you do too.

14:10.616 --> 14:11.484
Most of the Foundation figured

14:11.517 --> 14:13.453
you were
a government trap.

14:13.486 --> 14:15.455
‐ So why did you respond?

14:15.488 --> 14:17.657
‐ I have a good sense
for people,

14:17.690 --> 14:20.727
and I closely examined as many
of your personal accounts

14:20.760 --> 14:23.329
as I could access.

14:23.363 --> 14:26.332
We've never had someone
on the inside before.

14:26.366 --> 14:30.336
♪ ♪

14:30.370 --> 14:33.373
‐ This is everything
I got so far.

14:33.406 --> 14:35.708
Olivia Hughes was murdered.

14:35.742 --> 14:37.944
I just need your help
to find proof.

14:37.977 --> 14:41.381
‐ If I can get you proof
the NFFA killed this girl,

14:41.414 --> 14:43.516
the Foundation's gonna
wanna blast it wide.

14:43.549 --> 14:45.184
‐ Good.

14:45.218 --> 14:47.787
Her family deserves to know
what happened to her.

14:47.820 --> 14:51.958
♪ ♪

14:56.696 --> 14:59.732
Hey, wanna meet me
for lunch today?

14:59.766 --> 15:03.202
‐ Nah, I'm tired.
I didn't sleep.

15:03.236 --> 15:04.871
‐ You have therapy tonight,
right?

15:04.904 --> 15:06.839
‐ Not going.

15:06.873 --> 15:13.646
♪ ♪

15:13.679 --> 15:14.981
‐ [speaking Spanish]

15:15.014 --> 15:17.517
Sofie, come on.

15:17.550 --> 15:19.519
You have to try.

15:19.552 --> 15:21.687
Dr. Adams told me
you've stopped trying.

15:21.721 --> 15:23.523
‐ She's not supposed
to tell you that.

15:23.556 --> 15:25.358
Thought that was private.

15:25.391 --> 15:28.694
‐ Well, you're a minor
in an extreme case of trauma.

15:28.728 --> 15:29.662
She has to tell me.
‐ That's it.

15:29.695 --> 15:32.565
I'm done whining
to some stranger.

15:32.598 --> 15:35.701
‐ You need help that I don't
know how to give you myself.

15:37.069 --> 15:41.374
You're going to see
Dr. Adams tonight.

15:41.407 --> 15:43.443
Hmm?

15:43.476 --> 15:44.877
You're going tonight.

15:44.911 --> 15:47.547
♪ ♪

15:47.580 --> 15:49.749
Okay.

15:52.251 --> 15:59.091
♪ ♪

16:02.962 --> 16:05.932
[cell phone buzzing]

16:05.965 --> 16:12.905
♪ ♪

16:12.939 --> 16:15.041
‐ [groans]
Leave me alone.

16:15.074 --> 16:17.477
♪ ♪

16:17.510 --> 16:18.945
[cell phone chimes]

16:18.978 --> 16:21.948
[tense music]

16:21.981 --> 16:23.783
♪ ♪

16:23.816 --> 16:26.752
[cell phone buzzing]

16:26.786 --> 16:33.860
♪ ♪

16:36.696 --> 16:38.931
‐ Let's get to work.

16:38.965 --> 16:44.971
♪ ♪

17:05.057 --> 17:07.093
‐ Welcome, Miss Parker.
Enjoy your day.

17:07.126 --> 17:08.628
‐ Thanks.

17:08.661 --> 17:13.099
♪ ♪

17:13.132 --> 17:14.967
‐ Got eyes on target.

17:14.967 --> 17:16.569
Work fast.

17:16.602 --> 17:23.142
♪ ♪

17:23.175 --> 17:24.443
‐ We all clear?

17:24.477 --> 17:25.878
‐ Confirm the alarm
is deactivated.

17:25.912 --> 17:27.980
[lock clicks]

