a bill or something like that.

18:47.760 --> 18:49.128
This is way beyond.

18:49.161 --> 18:50.463
This is my house.

18:50.496 --> 18:52.465
‐ We had an agreement, Marcus.

18:52.498 --> 18:53.633
You want the name or not?

18:53.666 --> 18:55.635
[suspenseful music]

18:55.668 --> 18:57.803
‐ Okay.

18:57.837 --> 18:59.472
‐ Open the garage door.

18:59.505 --> 19:02.341
You don't want your neighbors
to see this.

19:02.375 --> 19:05.344
[gunfire]

19:05.378 --> 19:08.214
[men shouting]

19:11.217 --> 19:12.385
‐ Mm!
‐ Really?

19:12.418 --> 19:14.787
‐ Dude, you can't just send
your dudes on me like that.

19:14.820 --> 19:16.455
‐ Yeah, I can.
Whoo!

19:16.489 --> 19:17.590
‐ Annihilation complete.

19:17.623 --> 19:18.591
‐ [whines]
‐ There it is.

19:18.624 --> 19:21.160
[laughs]
You're such a lightweight.

19:21.193 --> 19:22.628
You should drink
every time we play.

19:22.662 --> 19:23.396
‐ I'm not even drunk.

19:25.665 --> 19:28.300
‐ Hey, so, um, she ever say
anything to you about me?

19:28.334 --> 19:31.170
‐ Who?
‐ Bonnie.

19:31.203 --> 19:34.140
You think we clicked, right?
‐ Dude, forget Bonnie.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.709
Kelen said she's getting
back with her ex.

19:36.742 --> 19:39.278
‐ [sighs]

19:40.413 --> 19:42.615
What'd I do?
I was nice.

19:42.648 --> 19:43.716
I asked questions.

19:43.749 --> 19:46.519
‐ Oh, well, maybe you could,
like, play it cool more

19:46.552 --> 19:49.789
and don't bring up
the Purge stuff so much.

19:49.822 --> 19:53.192
‐ So, what,
act all ashamed of myself,

19:53.225 --> 19:55.161
like you do?
‐ No, I don't.

19:55.194 --> 19:58.130
‐ You tell your girlfriend what
you bought for Purge night?

19:58.164 --> 20:00.466
‐ No, but I've been
reading that book

20:00.499 --> 20:03.202
you were talking about by the
woman who created the Purge.

20:03.235 --> 20:05.771
‐ Yeah?
It's great stuff, right?

20:05.805 --> 20:08.507
‐ Mm‐hmm, it says we're animals
born to hunt.

20:08.541 --> 20:10.643
‐ Yeah.

20:10.676 --> 20:12.478
We shouldn't let these
fucking college girls

20:12.511 --> 20:16.048
make us feel like shit about
doing what man was meant to do.

20:16.082 --> 20:17.216
‐ Right.

20:18.617 --> 20:21.220
You ever think about how weird
it is that, like,

20:21.253 --> 20:24.123
we have to wait
all year round to Purge?

20:24.156 --> 20:28.728
Like, how can something be good
one day and wrong the next?

20:28.761 --> 20:29.795
‐ Exactly.

20:31.197 --> 20:33.232
[suspenseful music]

20:33.265 --> 20:34.867
‐ You see on the news
about that farmer

20:34.900 --> 20:36.469
